    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (83.19) as our unequivocal anchor. Facing a favorable matchup against Lorenzen, **Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and a prime #2 spot in the order, positioning him to capitalize on his elite tools. Following closely, **Jacob Wilson** (74.08) presents significant upside; he faces the softest opposing arm of the day in Schultz (6.23 xERA). **Wilson**\u2019s aggressive placement at lead-off, combined with a 10% park advantage and a 19% SP skill cushion, makes him a primary engine for runs today. We are also monitoring **Miguel Vargas** (66.33), whose score is buoyed by a rare convergence of factors: a 10% park boost, a favorable SP profile, and notably, a 2% \"slow delivery\" bonus that elevates his stolen base potential\u2014a critical variable given our pursuit of speed.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Heliot Ramos** (53.59) on the bench. **Ramos** was a strong candidate for the final outfield slot, but he ultimately ceded the position to **Jackson Merrill** (53.94) and **Josh Lowe** (60.13), both of whom offered marginally higher efficiency in dynamic platoon settings. While **Marcell Ozuna** (53.57) received a slight wind-aided bump to his projections, the matchup against a high-tier arm like McClanahan necessitated a move toward more consistent daily contributors. We remain cautious regarding **Drake Baldwin**, as his score of 56.64 is based on a pending lineup; should he drop out of the #2 spot, his efficiency will shift significantly. Meanwhile, **Gunnar Henderson** (54.20) faces a challenging platoon disadvantage against Cantillo, serving as a reminder that even our stars must be managed against specific tactical hurdles.",
